        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:10PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bray, or 24 miles northeast of Mount Shasta, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deer Mountain Snow Park and Bray.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
